@colesbury you are right.

I did not consider the case where key exists in the shared keys table but old_value==NULL.
In that case, since the dict cannot use shared keys table, conversion to a combined table is necessary.

```
diff --git a/Objects/dictobject.c b/Objects/dictobject.c
index ac4a46dab10..e363253480b 100644
--- a/Objects/dictobject.c
+++ b/Objects/dictobject.c
@@ -1898,7 +1898,7 @@ insertdict(PyInterpreterState *interp, PyDictObject *mp,
             goto Fail;
     }

-    if (ix == DKIX_EMPTY) {
+    if (old_value == NULL) {
         // insert_combined_dict() will convert from non DICT_KEYS_GENERAL table
         // into DICT_KEYS_GENERAL table if key is not Unicode.
         // We don't convert it before _Py_dict_lookup because non-Unicode key
```
